                                               ✨ Al-Malik (ٱلْمَلِكُ) – Allah ka Naam ✨

Ma’ni (Meaning):

👉 Al-Malik ka matlab hai “Badshah, Hukmaran, Asal Malik aur Sovereign King”.
Allah hi asal Hukmaran hai jo poori kainaat par hukumat karta hai, uski hukumat mein na koi kami hai aur na koi shareek.

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

📖 Qur’an se Dalail:

1️⃣ Surah Taha (20:114)
"Fata’aalallahu Al-Malikul Haqq…"
➡ Matlab: Allah upar hai sab cheezon se, asal Badshah aur Haq.

2️⃣ Surah Aal-e-Imran (3:26)
"Qulillāhumma Mālikal-Mulk…"
➡ Matlab: Allah jisay chahe saltanat de aur jisay chahe le le.

3️⃣ Surah Mu’minoon (23:116)
"Fata’aalallahu Al-Malikul Haqq…"
➡ Matlab: Allah asal Badshah hai, uske siwa koi ilaah nahi.

4️⃣ Surah Hashr (59:23)
"Huwallāhul-Ladhī lā ilāha illā Huwal-Malikul Quddūs…"
➡ Matlab: Allah hi asal Malik hai, Paak hai aur uska hukm chalta hai.

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

🌸 Hadith se Dalail:

Nabi ﷺ ne farmaya:
"Qayamat ke din sab se bura naam hoga us shakhs ka jo apne aap ko ‘Malikul Amlak’ (King of kings) kahe."
(Sahih Bukhari 6205)

➡ Matlab: Allah hi asal King of Kings hai, insaan aisa da’wa nahi kar sakta.

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

💡 Asar aur Reflection:

Allah ki asal hukumat aur mulk par yaqeen rakhne se insaan kisi duniya ke hukmaran ya daulat par itimad nahi karta.
Wo samajhta hai ke izzat, zillat, daulat, saltanat – sab Allah ke haath mein hai.
Jo Allah ko Al-Malik samajhta hai wo insaan azad hota hai logon ki taqat aur duniya ke asraat se.

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

🌿 Practical Amal:

Roz “Yaa Malik” ka zikr karna dil mein yaqeen aur sukoon paida karta hai.
Apni maal-o-dawlat aur maqam ko Allah ki amanat samajh kar uske raste mein istemal karna.
Hamesha dua karna:
"Allahumma anta Al-Malikul Haqq, Rabb-ul-Arshil-Kareem, mujhe apne hukm ke mutabiq chalne ki taufeeq de."

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

✨ Khulaasa:
Al-Malik ka matlab hai asal aur hamesha ka Badshah jo hukumat mein shareek se paak hai. Uske hukm ke baghair kuch bhi nahi hota.
Us par yaqeen insaan ko dunya ke asraat se nikal kar akhirat ki asal zindagi ki taraf le jata hai.
